cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

The paper deals with resource allocation for device-to-device (D2D) communication in mobile networks, which is a topic related to network integration and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization problems and radio resource allocation, which are related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The use of relay nodes and the need for efficient resource allocation suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of relay-assisted D2D communication on network performance, which is related to security and privacy issues, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category as well.
